    81,
    'clytfibo90036g39q02dk4qsl',
    'BCSBD',
    'basalt-columns-sawn-bottom---drilled',
    'Basalt Columns Sawn Bottom - Drilled',
    unistr (
      '<ul><li>Origin: North America</li><li>Classification: Basalt </li><li>Color Range: Blacks, Greys</li><li>Finish: Natural</li><li>Application: Accents</li></ul>\u000d\u000a<p>Basalt Columns are large columnar rocks cored to be used as water features. Monolithic pieces of art, primarily gray in color with some brown or taupe color variations, sawn bottoms make for easy placement and reduced labor costs. These columns have been drilled to be used as water features. Group them in threes or more to create a unique and attractive water feature.\u000d\u000a</p>\u000d\u000a'
